The evidence with the title 'Why more than 80 million Americans won't vote on Election Day - vox ' says Nov 8, 2016  ... If you look at the Pew chart above , you'll notice a quirk: the vast majority of Americans who are registered to vote do show up to the polls , at least in presidential years . In 2012, around 84 percent of registered voters cast a ballot. The catch is that tens of millions of Americans simply are n't registered to begin  ... 
